# Kiyotaka Academy

> Institutional-grade education for the modern trader.

This file lists the canonical public articles. Each article is available as plain Markdown by appending `.md` to its URL.

## Modules

- [Order Flow Footprints](https://wiki.xapy.io/en/academy/order-flow-footprints): Read aggressive buyers and sellers in real time using footprint charts, bid-ask imbalance, and delta.
- [TPO & Profile](https://wiki.xapy.io/en/academy/tpo-profile): Time-Price Opportunity, market profile and value-area mechanics for context-driven decisions.
- [Technical Analysis](https://wiki.xapy.io/en/academy/technical-analysis): Trends, structure, levels and indicators — the modern technician's toolkit.
- [Psychology](https://wiki.xapy.io/en/academy/psychology): Risk discipline, emotional control and the cognitive frameworks used by institutional traders.
- [Options Greeks](https://wiki.xapy.io/en/academy/options-greeks)
- [Algorithmic](https://wiki.xapy.io/en/academy/algorithmic)

## Articles

- [HOW TO VIBECODE KSCRIPTS ON KIYOTAKA; NO PRIOR PROGRAMMING KNOWLEDGE REQUIRED, JUST AN IDEA IS SUFFICIENT](https://wiki.xapy.io/api/articles/en/algorithmic/how-to-vibecode-kscripts-on-kiyotaka-no-prior-programming-knowledge-required-just-an-idea-is-sufficient-mmauv7e6mayhxq): For years, custom indicators were locked behind paywalls, proprietary platforms, or the steep learning curve of mastering a scripting language most traders never had time to pick up. If you wanted a tool that thought the way you did one that measured exactly what you cared about you either paid someone to build it, spent months learning to code it yourself, or settled for whatever the platform gave you. Most traders settled. That changes with Kiyotaka_ai. By giving every trader a free, open editor to build and deploy custom indicators, Kiyotakaai has handed back something that was quietly gatekept for too long creative control over your own analysis. You no longer need to be a developer to think like one. You don’t need to retrofit your strategy into someone else’s indicator and hope it’s close enough. You can build exactly what you see in your head, test it on live charts, and trade with tools that are truly yours. This guide is about exactly that. We’re going to walk through how to vibe code indicators on Kiyotaka_ai no deep programming background required, just a clear idea, the right framework, and the willingness to iterate. By the end, you’ll have gone from concept to a working, plotted indicator on a live chart. And the best part? It won’t cost you a thing. Lets get the vibe coding started!!
